```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int = 3)
    if isa(dt, Date)
        throw(ArgumentError("timezone_bumper can only be applied to DateTime objects, not Date objects"))
    end
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end
```

This function `timezone_bumper` takes a `DateTime` object and an optional integer `bump` which represents the number of hours to add to the timestamp. If no `bump` is provided, it defaults to adding 3 hours. The function checks if the input `dt` is a `Date` object and throws an error if so, as the function is designed to work only with `DateTime` types.
